title: Trump committed fraud to exaggerate his wealth by up to $3.6bn, court rules
description: Donald Trump committed fraud for years while building the real estate empire that catapulted him to fame and the White House, a court has ruled.

title: Canadian Speaker resigns after inviting man who fought for Nazis to Zelenskyy speech
description: The Speaker of Canada's House of Commons has resigned after he invited a man who fought for the Nazis to attend a speech by Ukraine's president.

title: England will oppose playing Russian sides after UEFA lifts blanket ban
description: England will oppose playing matches against Russian football teams after UEFA lifted its blanket ban on the country taking part in its competitions to allow under-17s fixtures.

title: Putin critic Navalny loses appeal against extra 19-year jail sentence
description: Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny has lost his appeal against a 19-year sentence that was added to his existing jail term.

title: Top Russian admiral appears in video call - after Ukraine claimed he was 'killed' in missile strike
description: A top Russian admiral has appeared in a video call - a day after Ukrainian special forces claimed he had been killed in a missile strike.

title: Brown bear cubs dying in Japan due to salmon shortage
description: Brown bear cubs are starving to death in a remote part of northern Japan because pink salmon numbers are down.

title: Woman found dead on beach near Calais
description: A body of a migrant was found this morning on Sangatte beach near Calais.

title: 'We won't back down': Philippines warns China as row over disputed waters heats up
description: Tensions are growing between the Philippines and China as a dispute over a fiercely-contested fishing area in the South China Sea escalated on Tuesday.

title: Nelson Mandela's granddaughter dies
description: Zoleka Mandela, the granddaughter of the first president of South Africa Nelson Mandela, has died aged 43, the family has said.

title: Founder of popular photoblog slams Indian version in copyright row
description: The founder of the popular photoblog Humans of New York has hit out at an Indian version of his concept - Humans of Bombay - as it becomes embroiled in a copyright battle.

title: Mother whose sons died after she crashed into pond jailed for five years
description: A woman from Michigan has been sentenced to up to five years in prison after she crashed into an icy pond while intoxicated, killing her three young sons.

title: Death row inmate fights being 'test subject' for new execution method
description: A death row prisoner in Alabama is fighting plans for him to be the first person to be executed using nitrogen gas.

title: Explosion kills 20 and injures hundreds in Nagorno-Karabakh - as thousands flee over ethnic cleansing fears
description: At least 20 people have been killed and hundreds more injured in a powerful blast at a fuel depot in Nagorno-Karabakh.

title: Briton admits sexually abusing and killing dogs - as judge warns details could cause 'nervous shock'
description: A prominent British crocodile expert and academic has pleaded guilty to 56 charges of bestiality involving the rape, torture and killing of dogs.

title: Canadian parliament's standing ovation for former Nazi soldier was 'deeply embarrassing', Trudeau says
description: Canadian prime minister Justin Trudeau has said it is "deeply embarrassing" members of his parliament gave two standing ovations to a man who fought for the Nazis during the Second World War.
